Hey guys:
I've been living a nightmare lately. I have a big problem here with the cats. A deadly problem. But I might have found a cure - A Black Market cure. As you all know I take care of cats. Been doing so for 20 years. Unfortunately I've recently lost a couple cats - Pontiac and Navajo (2 and 1 years old) . I loved those two so much. Took us a while to get to the bottom of it, but as I suspected, and as some of you told me that you suspected, it turns out it is FIP (Feline infectious peritonitis). FIP is basically a 100% fatal virus, with no known cure - until now, maybe.. And I have another cat now with FIP - My Kiana. He's only 1 years old, and he will die if I don't do anything. He might even die if I do, but I have to try, right?

FIP is actually a coronavirus. It's not Covid-19, it's been around forever, but it is a corona strain. You've all heard of the Covid drug called remdesivir? Remdesivir has been proven to cure certain coronaviruses. Well it turns out that remdesivir also seems to cure, in many cases, cats with FIP. It's actually a miracle and a potential veterinary breakthrough. A virus that has always been deemed fatal, might finally have a cure.

U.S. hospitals have pretty much bought out the remdesivir supply, for covid. But now there is a black market version called GS441524. It is the exact same formula, and it is being used successfully to cure FIP in cats all across the world. I have found a legit source and have talked with many experts who have treated dozens of cats with this, and with great success.

The problem is that it is quite expensive. Over $1,000, in fact - and that's cheap for this. They need the formula for 3 months. I hate asking, I really do, but I could use some help. I just took Navajo and Kiana to the vet last week and the cost was $1,500 - and Navajo already passed away, and Kiana is now very sick. Literally anything helps. $10 helps. It really does. I'll post picks of the meds, and Kiana's progress. I appreciate anything very much. And I'll be straight with you, it might not work. But even a 50% chance is better than zero. And if it works I could possibly save other cats in the future - even yours. I have a GoFundMe and Paypal, both of which you can find in the attached link. Thank you, everyone.
